      "id": 42228,
      "kuerzel": "PFSec",
      "bezeichnung": "Platform Security",
      "planinhalt": "<p>This lecture is taught in the style of a seminar. The lecturer will provide an initial overview over the most important platforms and the relevant security aspects in the first part of the course.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The second part of the course will consist of talks given by the participants presenting current research papers from the area of Platform Security, followed by in-class discussions of the presentation subject. A list of possible papers for presentation will be provided. Participants can and are encouraged to propose papers and topics of their own choosing, subject to approval by the lecturer.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Due to the nature of the course, attendance in person is mandatory. Exceptions can be approved by the lecturer.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Also note that while there is no grade, in order to be allowed to take the exam M_PlFSec, participants need to successfully participate in the paper presentation activities with a presentation of their own in the same semester. The M_PIFSec exam will primarily consist of questions regarding the participant presentations in PFSec of the same semester.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Team presentations are possible, but require more papers to be presented, with the number of papers to be presented being equal to the number of team members.&nbsp;</p>",
